<subSubSection id="3B6142EDF3406A88037B7DE86DCE80E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FF864EB3F5E1F34D49C0572A680143AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AE90E7CE8DC34BAB567A0A5C498EB47" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The new section of 
<taxonomicName id="929CD6211BFFEE2D9BA76B14C5D0328F" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A41D9A08AC85CB3D887CFEF19D63F04D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subg. 
<emphasis id="3B874F9D8D6256527E24D047211A184C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
is characterized by its type, the dioicous 
<taxonomicName id="E1519671EDD9848A3905D35A4E94FC5A" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="CF3E7A7394C2EC53DE410A1F3CF4997D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="47CAFE4FA0BB096AB024CA411F929A5F" originalValue="Müll">Muell</normalizedToken>
. Frib. Distinctive features of 
<taxonomicName id="2816554F2119A4C12A80263BEFA2F393" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="C0656253665647284FB850ADCA3BB581" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="471487B616E44B1A2C8995FC83D65DA3" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32F14E5B90D5E08F7F4771ABCFE4DB34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="D40524834943410717E6818383E0E16F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Americanae</emphasis>
are thick-walled, pigmented stem epidermis cells with thinner-walled cells on the ventral side of the stem, closely and sharply ciliate-dentate leaf-margins, with largest teeth up to five cells long and terminal cells considerably longer than wide, leaf-lobes that are usually decurrent beyond the level of the keel, a verruculose or striate-verruculose cuticle, and two-celled gemmae at the margins of unmodified leaves. The dorsal leaf-lobes often develop an undulate or folded base and may even show minute lobules or auricles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CCFDD788102E33E286BF9C254C2AA00" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="type">
<paragraph id="F58628F578AA46B24510840106E407E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4FAABA05704F8B6C37CFB4C85817E13A" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="158BE8779A73155A590C045C20B05D5B" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="AD1A59178362E3AF164D0BB9A1DD0E6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="1D001C05E7D19DBCE4A10816365C34FD" originalValue="Müll">Muell</normalizedToken>
. Frib., Bull. Herb. Boissier, 
<normalizedToken id="F316847F77A95F7CEEEA0C03A5980CE8" originalValue="sér">ser</normalizedToken>
. 2, 3: 44. 1902.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B0DDCEA97668C91A83AFD98ACCC9A8" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="note">
<paragraph id="6B899942B93C49F30FB5FEC75F7D9E5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C389C9E89132197AAC04DD6ED1FDC293" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="1EC499C9CCD30640A669C92158B0AD53" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="C68D7EA6B49CCCE38A6E6835B54F67B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed sister to 
<taxonomicName id="D07029446C596A4D7F298665F219C4D2" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="860C1CCF884B3CF32707C285D68F93EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B1B4A2A5160C6E446DD43D1441D24B58" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Compactae</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="0BABAFF360E56585CC294C54FA9A32E2" originalValue="Müll">Muell</normalizedToken>
. Frib.) H. Buch with weak bootstrap support (
<bibRefCitation id="282614A7EC82097EF9FB891D0FC957CF" author="Heinrichs, J" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" pagination="973 - 985" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" refId="B2" refString="Heinrichs, J, Bombosch, A, Feldberg, K, Kreier, HP, Hentschel, J, Eckstein, J, Long, D, Zhu, RL, Schaefer-Verwimp, A, Schmidt, AR, Shaw, B, Shaw, AJ, Vana, J, 2012. A phylogeny of the northern temperate leafy liverwort genus Scapania (Scapaniaceae, Jungermanniales). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 62: 973 - 985, 10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" title="A phylogeny of the northern temperate leafy liverwort genus Scapania (Scapaniaceae, Jungermanniales)." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.029" volume="62" year="2012">Heinrichs et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from members of 
<taxonomicName id="D81ABA0013E24BB5F1F516B09A7C1496" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CB27E05A5599DB55DD51697B0A558AE1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="BCB230A1932FA9DF1F06DA3F775D27D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Compactae</emphasis>
by its dioicous condition; hence we place it in a new section rather 
<pageBreakToken id="09C14F938F29127BF0776B97D84CE041" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" start="start">than</pageBreakToken>
in sect. 
<taxonomicName id="14EEC4805D8286008AD09A5B8144468D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Compactae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2E1369A2ADC4E0877EAF10787979BDD7" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Compactae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In our current circumscription, 
<taxonomicName id="827660A95E1C5662BFB269086358CF4B" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8382A9E85D6AA64BCA95D6936A933E7" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="31081B450DEDC55494A19D0D2E69C573" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Americanae</emphasis>
is monospecific, however, extension of the taxon sampling in forthcoming molecular studies may disclose further representatives.
</paragraph>
